---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const transcript = {
  title: 'Superbiologics: The Future of Joint Repair',
  subtitle: 'Novel Cells, Growth Factors, and Cross-Species Tissue Engineering',
  category: 'Research',
  duration: '2:00',
  relatedResearch: '/research/anabolic-therapies',
  relatedVideo: '/videos#educational',
};
---

<Layout title={transcript.title + " - Transcript"}>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="bg-stone-900 text-white py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <a href="/transcripts" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-stone-400 hover:text-white text-sm mb-6 transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
        </svg>
        All Transcripts
      </a>
      
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="text-xs px-3 py-1 bg-purple-500/20 text-purple-300 rounded-full">{transcript.category}</span>
        <span class="text-stone-400 text-sm">{transcript.duration}</span>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="font-display text-display-sm md:text-display-md text-white mb-3">
        {transcript.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-stone-300">{transcript.subtitle}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Transcript Content -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-purple-500 p-6 mb-8 not-prose">
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
            <strong class="text-stone-900">The Vision:</strong> Moving beyond simple tissue replacement to 
            "super biologic enhancements" that combine the best of stem cells, growth factors, and even 
            cross-species tissue engineering to create superior replacement solutions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-stone-900 mb-4">Full Transcript</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p class="timestamp-text">
            <span class="timestamp">[00:00]</span>
            We are all aware of the risk of cancer, but there's another disease that's destined to affect 
            even more of us: arthritis. Cancer may kill you, but when you look at the numbers, arthritis 
            ruins more lives.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Assuming you live a long life, there's a 50% chance you'll develop arthritis, and it's not 
            just aging that causes arthritis. Common injuries can lead to decades of pain until our joints 
            quite literally grind to a halt.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 p-5 rounded-sm my-6 not-prose">
            <p class="text-stone-800 font-medium mb-2">The Statistics</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">
              <strong>50% of people</strong> who live a long life will develop arthritis. Injuries sustained 
              in youth can lead to decades of progressive joint damage.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <p>
            Desperate for a solution, we've turned to engineering to design artificial components to replace 
            our worn out body parts. But in the midst of a modern buzz around the promises of a bionic body, 
            shouldn't we stop and ask if there's a better, more natural way?
          </p>
          
          <p class="timestamp-text">
            <span class="timestamp">[00:45]</span>
            Let's consider an alternative path. What if all the replacements our bodies need already exist 
            in nature or within our own stem cells?
          </p>
          
          <p>
            This is the field of biologic replacements where we replace worn out parts with new natural ones. 
            For instance, in your worn out knee, we create new cartilage using a paste graft of your own 
            stem cells, and replace the meniscus and ligaments with ones from a donor.
          </p>
          
          <p class="timestamp-text">
            <span class="timestamp">[01:10]</span>
            We are now moving into <strong>super biologic enhancements</strong> where we add novel cells 
            and growth factors to the biologic replacement tissues.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            And our options extend beyond human tissue. By treating animal tissue and seamlessly integrating 
            the best elements of the animal kingdom into our human anatomy, we create super biologic 
            replacement solutions and merge the best of evolution from different species.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Key Concepts -->
        <div class="mt-10 not-prose">
          <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-stone-900 mb-6">The Superbiologics Framework</h3>
          
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-sm">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold">1</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-medium text-stone-900 mb-1">Biologic Replacements</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">Replace worn parts with natural tissuesâ€”paste grafts from your 
                own cells, donor meniscus and ligaments.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-sm">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold">2</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-medium text-stone-900 mb-1">Super Biologic Enhancements</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">Add novel cells and growth factors to biologic tissues to 
                enhance healing and integration.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-sm">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-purple-600 font-bold">3</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-medium text-stone-900 mb-1">Cross-Species Integration</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">Treat and integrate animal tissues to merge the best 
                evolutionary solutions from different species.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Links -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-stone-50 border-t border-stone-200">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-stone-900 mb-6">Related Content</h3>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href={transcript.relatedResearch} class="p-5 bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-sm hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors group">
          <span class="text-xs text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Research</span>
          <p class="font-display text-stone-900 group-hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors mt-1">Anabolic Therapies Studies</p>
        </a>
        <a href={transcript.relatedVideo} class="p-5 bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-sm hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors group">
          <span class="text-xs text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Video</span>
          <p class="font-display text-stone-900 group-hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors mt-1">Watch Full Video</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .timestamp {
    @apply text-xs font-mono text-purple-600 bg-purple-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mr-2;
  }
</style>
